{
  "text": "Definition of the process-oriented training: In order to improve attitudes of health professionals the training was based on evidence, practical skills and reflective processes (both private and professional experiences) in relation to breastfeeding and parental support. To ensure that the healthcare professionals would be ready to meet the demands of their profession they were trained in problem solving, self-reflection, and decision-making (in terms of competence), and their personal qualifications evaluated [CITATION_1] ).",
